No test files. Now let me reason through each fix:

**Fix 1** (Line 71): `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}` — The value `plain` exists in both old and new type unions. No change needed.

**Fix 2** (Line 68): The `<Button>` contains only `<MinusCircleIcon />` as children (line 77). Per the fix instructions, when Button contains only an icon element from `@patternfly/react-icons`, move it to the `icon` prop and make the element self-closing. So:
```jsx
// Before:
<Button
  data-test="delete-row"
  aria-label={tooltipDeleteRow || t('Remove')}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  type={ButtonType.button}
  isInline
  onClick={!disableDeleteRow ? onDelete : undefined}
  isAriaDisabled={disableDeleteRow}
>
  <MinusCircleIcon />
</Button>

// After:
<Button
  data-test="delete-row"
  aria-label={tooltipDeleteRow || t('Remove')}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  type={ButtonType.button}
  isInline
  onClick={!disableDeleteRow ? onDelete : undefined}
  isAriaDisabled={disableDeleteRow}
  icon={<MinusCircleIcon />}
/>
```

**Fix 3** (Line 3): Advisory about Tooltip's Popper behavioral change. This is a test-impact warning. No test files exist for this component. The Tooltip usage itself doesn't need code changes — this is about test queries. No change needed.

